                <h3>What is loneliness?</h3>
                <p2>
                    Loneliness is commonly associated with negative feelings like feeling isolated, depressed, stressed or anxious. The dictionary meaning of loneliness is sadness because of not having any company or friends. A person usually feels lonely when they have not spoken to anyone for a very long time or have not been around people. There are instances when a person tends to feel lonely even when they are around people. It is not about the quantity of friends you have in life but the quality matters.
                </p2>
